04:14.515 --> 04:17.450
[ INSECTS CHIRPING ]

04:17.450 --> 04:19.586
[ DOOR OPENS ]

04:23.657 --> 04:25.191
WHAT IS IT?

04:25.191 --> 04:27.260
HOW CAN YOU STAY IN BED
ALL DAY AND ALL NIGHT?

04:27.260 --> 04:30.330
I WANTED TO SEE
WHAT IT FEELS LIKE TO BE YOU.

04:30.330 --> 04:31.598
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

04:31.598 --> 04:35.869
YOU'RE BLONDE, DARLING,
BUT YOU'RE NOT SLOW.

04:35.869 --> 04:38.371
WE NEED TO TALK.

04:38.371 --> 04:41.508
UNLESS YOU'RE TELLING ME THAT
YOU'RE GONNA BE HIT BY A BUS

04:41.508 --> 04:44.645
IN THE NEXT FEW MINUTES,
WE HAVE NOTHING TO TALK ABOUT.

04:44.645 --> 04:47.247
CAN YOU DROP THE SARCASM
FOR ONE MINUTE?

04:47.247 --> 04:49.683
WE NEED TO TALK.

04:53.119 --> 04:54.788
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

04:54.788 --> 04:56.857
YOU NEED TO HAVE
A CONVERSATION WITH AMANDA.

04:56.857 --> 04:59.626
I'M NOT READY
TO TALK TO HER RIGHT NOW.

04:59.626 --> 05:01.535
WHY?

05:01.535 --> 05:04.938
BECAUSE I'M NOT.

05:04.938 --> 05:07.974
KATHERYN, I DIDN'T COME IN HERE
TO ARGUE WITH YOU.

05:07.974 --> 05:09.375
THEN WHY ARE YOU
IN MY PRESENCE?

05:10.476 --> 05:13.246
THE VERY SIGHT OF YOU
MAKES ME WANT TO ARGUE.

05:13.246 --> 05:15.381
BECAUSE YOUR DAUGHTER
NEEDS YOU.

05:15.381 --> 05:17.984
AND I HAVE NEEDS, TOO.

05:19.052 --> 05:22.488
HOW CAN YOU BE
SO UNBELIEVABLY SELFISH?

05:23.857 --> 05:26.426
THAT HAD TO HURT
FALLING FROM YOUR LIPS.

05:26.426 --> 05:27.728
OHH.

05:27.728 --> 05:31.097
CONSIDERING YOU ARE THE MOST
SELFISH, SELF‐CENTERED BASTARD

05:31.097 --> 05:33.233
I HAVE EVER HAD
THE DISPLEASURE OF KNOWING.

05:33.233 --> 05:36.069
YOUR DAUGHTER IS FALLING APART
RIGHT NOW IN THE OTHER ROOM

05:36.069 --> 05:38.672
BECAUSE SHE IS WAITING TO HEAR
WHAT YOU ARE THINKING.

05:38.672 --> 05:42.242
SHE IS GOING TO HAVE TO WAIT
JUST A LITTLE BIT LONGER.

05:42.242 --> 05:43.744
OH, THAT IS SO YOU.

05:43.744 --> 05:44.745
YES...

05:44.745 --> 05:46.246
AND THAT IS SO YOU.

05:46.246 --> 05:47.581
WHAT DOES THAT EVEN MEAN?

05:47.581 --> 05:50.083
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
WHAT IS SO ME?

05:50.083 --> 05:52.719
YOU COME RUNNING TO ME
WITH HELP WITH THE KIDS

05:52.719 --> 05:53.987
WHEN YOU'RE SCARED...

05:53.987 --> 05:56.857
WHEN YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO DO OR WHAT TO SAY.

05:56.857 --> 05:58.692
REALLY?
YES.

05:58.692 --> 06:00.260
I COME RUNNING TO YOU?

06:00.260 --> 06:01.768
YOU LEAVE THEM IN SHAMBLES,

06:01.768 --> 06:04.137
AND YOU WAIT FOR ME
TO PICK UP THE PIECES.

06:04.137 --> 06:06.907
WELL, JIM, RIGHT NOW,

06:06.907 --> 06:09.810
I DON'T HAVE THE STRENGTH
TO PICK UP THE PIECES

06:09.810 --> 06:11.444
FOR ANYONE ELSE BUT MYSELF.

06:11.444 --> 06:13.013
WELL, YOU BETTER FIND
THE DAMN STRENGTH

06:13.013 --> 06:15.081
TO PICK UP THE PIECES
FOR SOMEONE OTHER THAN YOURSELF.

06:15.081 --> 06:16.382
AND YOU BETTER DO IT
RIGHT NOW

06:16.382 --> 06:18.051
BECAUSE YOUR DAUGHTER
NEEDS YOU RIGHT NOW.

06:18.051 --> 06:21.187
GET OUT OF BED
AND GO TALK TO YOUR DAUGHTER.

06:21.187 --> 06:23.256
YOU DON'T GET IT.

06:24.825 --> 06:26.627
WHAT?
I DON'T GET WHAT?

06:28.194 --> 06:29.863
THIS IS YOUR FAULT.

06:29.863 --> 06:31.698
MY FAULT?

06:31.698 --> 06:33.399
YES.

06:36.202 --> 06:38.672
YOU ARE SOME PIECE OF WORK,
YOU KNOW THAT?

06:38.672 --> 06:41.441
NO, I'M TELLING YOU
THE TRUTH.

06:42.509 --> 06:44.611
SO MY DAUGHTER,

06:44.611 --> 06:47.480
SOMEONE THAT I LOVE
MORE THAN I LOVE LIFE ITSELF,

06:47.480 --> 06:48.815
TRIES TO KILL HERSELF,

06:48.815 --> 06:50.684
AND SOMEHOW
THAT IS MY FAULT?

06:50.684 --> 06:52.919
MY LITTLE GIRL,
MY DAUGHTER.

06:52.919 --> 06:54.655
HOW IS THAT, KATHERYN?
HOW IS IT?

06:54.655 --> 06:56.489
BECAUSE SEVEN
IS SOMEONE'S DAUGHTER.

06:56.489 --> 06:57.490
OH, COME ON!

06:57.490 --> 06:58.559
AND EIGHT...
REALLY?

06:58.559 --> 06:59.593
...AND NINE.

06:59.593 --> 07:01.535
WE'RE GONNA TALK
ABOUT THIS AGAIN?

07:01.535 --> 07:04.037
THE WAY YOU TREAT
THESE GIRLS, JIM ‐‐

07:04.037 --> 07:06.172
THE INS AND THE OUTS,

07:06.172 --> 07:08.274
THE AFFAIRS,

07:08.274 --> 07:10.911
THE DISRESPECT FOR WOMEN ‐‐
[ SCOFFS ]

07:10.911 --> 07:13.880
...IT'S ALL COMING BACK TO HAUNT
YOU IN YOUR DAUGHTER'S BEDROOM.

07:13.880 --> 07:15.181
YOU'RE DELUSIONAL.

07:15.181 --> 07:17.117
I'M DELUSIONAL?
YES, YOU'RE DELUSIONAL.

07:17.117 --> 07:19.185
I'M DELUSIONAL?
YOU DON'T REALIZE IT?

07:19.185 --> 07:20.687
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

07:20.687 --> 07:23.389
EVERYTHING THAT
YOU ARE DOING OUT THERE

07:23.389 --> 07:25.859
IS COMING BACK TO YOU
THROUGH YOUR DAUGHTER,

07:25.859 --> 07:28.562
THROUGH OUR CHILDREN.

07:28.562 --> 07:31.131
AND JUST WHAT THE HELL
DO YOU THINK YOU ARE?

07:31.131 --> 07:33.066
THE VIRGIN MOTHER?

07:33.066 --> 07:34.467
YOU THINK
YOU HAVEN'T SINNED?

07:34.467 --> 07:37.003
YOU HONESTLY CAN LAY HERE
IN THIS BED DAY IN AND DAY OUT

07:37.003 --> 07:38.572
AND TELL ME
YOU HAVEN'T DONE ANYTHING

07:38.572 --> 07:40.240
TO BRING ANY OF THIS
UPON OUR HOUSEHOLD?

07:40.240 --> 07:41.875
NO, I HAVE DONE NOTHING.
REALLY?

07:41.875 --> 07:43.777
I HAVE DONE NOTHING
BUT LOVE YOU.

07:43.777 --> 07:44.778
OH!

07:44.778 --> 07:46.479
I'VE TRIED
TO BE A GOOD WIFE.

07:46.479 --> 07:48.649
I TRIED
TO STAND BY YOUR SIDE.

07:48.649 --> 07:49.650
OH, GEEZ.
BUT NO.

07:49.650 --> 07:50.617
I'M SORRY.

07:50.617 --> 07:53.119
I WASN'T GOOD ENOUGH
FOR JAMES CRYER.

07:53.119 --> 07:54.788
OH, MY GOODNESS.
IT'S TIME FOR A PITY PARTY.

07:54.788 --> 07:56.289
LET ME GET MY HAT.
NO, NOT PITY.

07:56.289 --> 07:58.091
THIS IS A PARTY!

07:59.793 --> 08:02.869
I KNOW YOU MARRIED ME
FOR MY NAME

08:02.869 --> 08:05.572
AND MY FAMILY'S GOOD STANDING.

08:05.572 --> 08:07.708
OH, I KNOW IT.

08:09.175 --> 08:12.913
AND I KNOW YOU'RE STILL WITH ME,
JUST RIDING THAT NAME.

08:12.913 --> 08:14.314
[ SOBS ]

08:14.314 --> 08:16.249
I KNEW IT THEN...

08:16.249 --> 08:18.652
AND I HAVE ENDURED HELL
FROM YOU.

08:18.652 --> 08:21.354
BUT I SWEAR TO YOU,

08:21.354 --> 08:24.357
I WILL NOT LET YOU LEAVE

08:24.357 --> 08:27.093
UNTIL YOU HAVE ENDURED
AS MUCH HELL FROM ME

08:27.093 --> 08:29.095
AS YOU HAVE GIVEN ME.

08:32.633 --> 08:33.800
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

08:33.800 --> 08:35.802
I UNDERSTAND
LOUD AND CLEAR.

08:35.802 --> 08:40.941
SO, WHILE YOU ARE SITTING AROUND
IN YOUR BED, HATING ME,

08:40.941 --> 08:42.342
TRYING TO FIGURE OUT A WAY

08:42.342 --> 08:44.711
TO MAKE ME PLAN
MY OWN PERSONAL TRIP TO HELL

08:44.711 --> 08:47.280
WHILE YOUR DAUGHTER
IS SITTING IN THE OTHER ROOM

08:47.280 --> 08:48.715
HURTING HERSELF,

08:48.715 --> 08:50.483
I WANT YOU TO REMEMBER
ONE THING ‐‐

08:50.483 --> 08:53.687
SHE IS OUR DAUGHTER.
SHE NEEDS YOU.

08:53.687 --> 08:56.823
SO, WHEN YOU COME OFF
OF YOUR HIGH HORSE,

08:56.823 --> 08:58.925
PLEASE,
WHEN YOU HAVE A MOMENT,

08:58.925 --> 09:02.903
GO IN THERE
AND HUG YOUR DAUGHTER.

09:02.903 --> 09:05.672
GET OUT OF MY ROOM!

09:08.441 --> 09:10.310
LOVE TO.

09:12.312 --> 09:13.413
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

09:16.550 --> 09:19.152
[ GROANS SOFTLY ]

09:30.931 --> 09:32.265
HI.

09:32.265 --> 09:33.700
YOU WANTED TO SEE ME?

09:33.700 --> 09:38.939
YES. I DIDN'T WANT TO HAVE THIS
CONVERSATION OVER THE PHONE.

09:38.939 --> 09:40.440
WHAT IS IT?

09:40.440 --> 09:43.209
YOU SHOULD OPEN DISCOVERY
ON THE YOUNG CASE.

09:43.209 --> 09:44.878
I ALREADY DID THAT.

09:44.878 --> 09:46.813
HAVE YOU RECEIVED IT ALL
FROM THE D. A.?

09:46.813 --> 09:47.814
YES.

09:47.814 --> 09:49.550
HOW DOES THAT CASE LOOK?

09:49.550 --> 09:52.519
LIKE HE WAS FRAMED.
LIKE THE "MONA LISA."

09:52.519 --> 09:53.954
IT'S ALL PERFECT.

09:53.954 --> 09:56.456
YOU SHOULD OPEN DISCOVERY.

09:56.456 --> 09:58.625
I JUST SAID
I ALREADY DID THAT.

09:58.625 --> 10:03.003
PERSONALLY EXAMINE
ALL OF THE EVIDENCE.

10:03.003 --> 10:06.673
IF I EXAMINE
ALL OF THIS EVIDENCE

10:06.673 --> 10:10.176
AND I FIND
THERE ARE OTHERS INVOLVED,

10:10.176 --> 10:12.513
SHOULD I TURN MY BACK?

10:12.513 --> 10:15.081
NO, DON'T TURN YOUR BACK.

10:15.081 --> 10:18.184
JUST LOOK THE OTHER WAY.

10:18.184 --> 10:20.554
HMM. LOOK THE OTHER WAY?

10:20.554 --> 10:22.055
YES.

10:22.055 --> 10:24.891
AND WHEN I TURN
IN THAT DIRECTION,

10:24.891 --> 10:26.893
WOULD I FIND YOU AND JIM?

10:26.893 --> 10:32.032
EXAMINE THE EVIDENCE
AND LOOK THE OTHER WAY.

10:32.032 --> 10:35.669
WHAT YOU ARE ASKING ME TO DO
IS BEYOND UNETHICAL.

10:35.669 --> 10:38.138
NO, I AM ASKING YOU
AS YOUR HUSBAND,

10:38.138 --> 10:42.275
PLEASE, FOR THE SAKE
OF THE STATE,

10:42.275 --> 10:44.377
EXAMINE THE EVIDENCE

10:44.377 --> 10:47.113
AND LET THIS BE A BYGONE.

10:48.549 --> 10:49.983
ALL RIGHT.

10:49.983 --> 10:53.219
I WILL EVALUATE
THE EVIDENCE.

10:53.219 --> 10:55.088
AND?

10:55.088 --> 10:58.224
AND I WILL LET YOU KNOW
WHAT MY NEXT MOVE IS.

11:00.293 --> 11:03.036
SWEETHEART...

11:03.036 --> 11:05.138
I LOVE YOU
MORE THAN YOU KNOW,

11:05.138 --> 11:07.908
AND I AM SINCERELY SORRY.

11:08.975 --> 11:10.544
I'LL SEE YOU AT HOME.

11:30.463 --> 11:32.633
YOU LOOK BETTER.

11:32.633 --> 11:34.467
I FEEL BETTER.

11:34.467 --> 11:36.503
GOOD.

11:38.238 --> 11:40.774
HANNA, I'M NEVER GOING TO
BE ABLE TO REPAY YOU.

11:40.774 --> 11:43.376
MM.
YOU DON'T OWE ME NOTHING.

11:43.376 --> 11:46.446
YEAH, I DO.
NO, YOU DON'T.

11:46.446 --> 11:48.982
YOU CAME IN HERE
AND TOOK CARE OF ME

11:48.982 --> 11:50.684
LIKE I WAS YOUR VERY OWN.

11:53.854 --> 11:55.421
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

11:57.591 --> 11:58.992
YEAH.

12:00.493 --> 12:02.769
YEAH, I'M FINE.

12:10.977 --> 12:13.413
MRS. CRYER,
I NEED TO TELL YOU SOMETHING.

12:13.413 --> 12:14.781
WHAT IS IT?

12:19.452 --> 12:21.622
WHEN I STARTED WORKING HERE,

12:21.622 --> 12:23.323
AND THE DAY THAT GIRL,
CANDACE...

12:23.323 --> 12:26.126
NINE.
...SHOWED UP...

12:27.193 --> 12:28.529
I'M SORRY?

12:30.831 --> 12:32.899
NINE.
I CALL HER NINE.

12:32.899 --> 12:34.467
GO ON.

12:34.467 --> 12:37.904
WELL, I DIDN'T KNOW HOW
TO TELL YOU

12:37.904 --> 12:41.542
BECAUSE I DIDN'T WANT TO
LOSE MY JOB...

12:43.476 --> 12:45.912
...BUT CANDACE
IS MY DAUGHTER.

12:49.850 --> 12:52.886
NINE IS YOUR DAUGHTER?

12:52.886 --> 12:55.321
WHAT?

12:57.991 --> 12:59.526
NEVER MIND.

13:04.170 --> 13:05.806
SHE'S YOUR DAUGHTER?

13:05.806 --> 13:07.674
YEAH.

13:09.576 --> 13:12.579
I WAS SO EMBARRASSED
WHEN I FIRST SAW HER.

13:12.579 --> 13:14.214
[ SIGHING ]

13:14.214 --> 13:15.916
SHE'S BECOME
SUCH AN AWFUL PERSON.

13:15.916 --> 13:17.317
AND THEN SHE WAS
WITH AMANDA,

13:17.317 --> 13:20.086
AND ‐‐ AND SHE WAS TELLING
ALL THOSE LIES ABOUT ME,

13:20.086 --> 13:22.022
SAYING I WAS DEAD.

13:22.022 --> 13:23.990
I AM SO SORRY.

13:23.990 --> 13:25.992
I'VE DONE MY BEST
WITH HER.

13:25.992 --> 13:27.861
SHE JUST WON'T DO
THE RIGHT THING.

13:29.663 --> 13:32.766
PLEASE TRY NOT TO BE
TOO MAD WITH ME.

13:35.068 --> 13:36.903
YOU SPILLED A DRINK ON HER.

13:36.903 --> 13:38.304
[ SCOFFS ]

13:38.304 --> 13:41.842
IT WAS ALL I COULD DO NOT TO
GET MY HANDS AROUND HER THROAT.

13:43.910 --> 13:47.180
YOU SHOULD HAVE TOLD ME.

13:47.180 --> 13:49.215
WELL, I WANTED TO.

13:49.215 --> 13:52.218
AND I KNOW SHE WAS
JUST LOOKING OUT FOR ME,

13:52.218 --> 13:54.721
BUT CELINE SAID NOT TO.
FOUR.

13:54.721 --> 13:57.123
WHAT?

13:58.191 --> 14:00.534
FOUR SAID NOT TO.

14:00.534 --> 14:01.602
CELINE?

14:01.602 --> 14:02.903
YES.

14:02.903 --> 14:06.472
THE SAME CELINE THAT WAS
SLEEPING WITH MY HUSBAND.

14:07.608 --> 14:10.243
WHAT?

14:10.243 --> 14:12.212
YES, SHE WAS.

14:12.212 --> 14:14.380
AND SHE'S STILL
WORKING HERE?

14:14.380 --> 14:16.416
YES.

14:16.416 --> 14:19.019
THEY THINK I DON'T KNOW.

14:19.019 --> 14:20.486
MRS. CRYER.

14:20.486 --> 14:22.556
YES?

14:22.556 --> 14:25.225
WHY WOULD YOU LET HER
STAY HERE IN YOUR HOUSE?

14:26.292 --> 14:28.695
BECAUSE I'M ENJOYING IT.

14:30.597 --> 14:33.333
I'M ENJOYING
WATCHING HER SUFFER.

14:34.668 --> 14:37.270
JIM DOESN'T GIVE HER
A SECOND GLANCE.

14:37.270 --> 14:40.974
SHE'S SO UPSET ABOUT IT.

14:40.974 --> 14:44.611
SHE'S NOT YOUNG ANYMORE.

14:44.611 --> 14:48.348
I ENJOY WATCHING HER GET OLD
AND BE MISERABLE.

14:49.415 --> 14:51.685
JIM WON'T EVEN LOOK AT HER,

14:51.685 --> 14:54.287
AND SHE IS DEVASTATED.

14:55.789 --> 14:59.526
OH, I KNOW IT'S WRONG FOR ME
TO FEEL THIS WAY,

14:59.526 --> 15:01.835
BUT THIS IS A GIFT.

15:01.835 --> 15:04.104
[ CHUCKLES ]

15:04.104 --> 15:06.840
HOW MANY WOMEN CAN SAY
THEY GET TO WATCH

15:06.840 --> 15:09.776
THEIR HUSBAND'S MISTRESSES
GO THROUGH HELL?

15:09.776 --> 15:11.978
MM.

15:11.978 --> 15:14.615
SOME OF WHAT YOU'RE SAYING
MAKES SENSE.

15:14.615 --> 15:16.517
BUT AIN'T NO WAY
IN THE WORLD

15:16.517 --> 15:19.485
I WOULD ALLOW MY HUSBAND'S WHORE
TO BE IN MY HOUSE.

15:19.485 --> 15:21.354
WELL...

15:21.354 --> 15:23.657
HE TRIED TO GET RID OF HER.

15:23.657 --> 15:26.226
BUT I WANT HIM
TO SEE HIS MISTAKE

15:26.226 --> 15:29.129
EVERY TIME HE WALKS
THROUGH THAT DOOR.

15:30.564 --> 15:33.567
SEE,
NOW I UNDERSTAND IT ALL.

15:33.567 --> 15:35.301
I BET YOU DO.

15:36.803 --> 15:39.072
AND I DO, TOO.

15:40.206 --> 15:42.976
SOME THINK SEVEN ROUNDS
OF CANCER

15:42.976 --> 15:45.679
WILL MAKE YOU RETHINK
YOUR LIFE.

15:45.679 --> 15:48.582
WHAT HAVE YOU BEEN
RETHINKING?

15:49.650 --> 15:51.985
MISTAKES.

15:51.985 --> 15:54.420
I WANT DO‐OVERS.

15:54.420 --> 15:56.757
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

15:56.757 --> 15:59.159
I WAS 20 YESTERDAY.

15:59.159 --> 16:01.334
YOU BEEN SMOKING
MORE WEED?

16:01.334 --> 16:02.503
[ CHUCKLES ]

16:02.503 --> 16:04.971
NOW, LISTEN TO ME.

16:07.240 --> 16:10.310
I WAS 20 YESTERDAY, HANNA.

16:12.245 --> 16:14.280
I WAS YOUNG.

16:14.280 --> 16:16.617
I WAS HAPPY.

16:20.086 --> 16:22.322
WHERE'D THE TIME GO, HMM?

16:24.424 --> 16:26.392
LIFE.

16:26.392 --> 16:28.995
I RESENT JIM SO MUCH.

16:28.995 --> 16:31.865
HE STOLE IT FROM ME.

16:31.865 --> 16:33.934
STOLE WHAT?

16:33.934 --> 16:36.436
HE STOLE MY YOUTH...

16:36.436 --> 16:38.772
PRETENDING TO LOVE ME.

16:38.772 --> 16:41.575
I LOVED HIM...

16:41.575 --> 16:43.544
ADORED HIM.

16:43.544 --> 16:45.712
I DOTED ON HIM.
I GAVE HIM EVERYTHING.

16:45.712 --> 16:48.048
I WENT TO BAT WITH MY FATHER
OVER HIM.

16:49.215 --> 16:52.385
THERE IS NOTHING SADDER
THAN BEING IN YOUR 50s

16:52.385 --> 16:56.122
AND REALIZING THE MAN
THAT YOU LOVED AND ADORED

16:56.122 --> 16:58.358
WAS A THIEF
TO STEAL YOUR YOUTH.

16:58.358 --> 17:00.500
AND WHEN YOU GET OLD...

17:00.500 --> 17:02.202
[ SNIFFLES ]

17:02.202 --> 17:05.105
...HE WOULD TRADE YOU
IN FOR SOMEONE ELSE.

17:11.578 --> 17:13.246
SO...

17:13.246 --> 17:17.050
[ LAUGHS ]

17:17.050 --> 17:19.620
[ SNIFFLES ]

17:19.620 --> 17:22.422
...NINE IS YOUR DAUGHTER?

17:22.422 --> 17:25.992
WHAT IS THIS
"NINE" BUSINESS?

17:25.992 --> 17:27.961
SHE'S SLEEPING
WITH MY HUSBAND.

17:27.961 --> 17:30.096
WHO ‐‐ WHAT?

17:31.865 --> 17:33.499
YES.

17:33.499 --> 17:36.302
CLOSE YOUR MOUTH, HANNA.

17:36.302 --> 17:38.238
[ SIGHS ]

17:40.774 --> 17:41.808
[ SNIFFLES ]

17:41.808 --> 17:43.510
I'M SO SORRY.

17:43.510 --> 17:46.012
I DON'T KNOW
WHY YOU'RE UPSET.

17:46.012 --> 17:47.480
I...

17:47.480 --> 17:49.449
[ STUTTERS ]

17:51.918 --> 17:54.120
HOW CAN YOU BE SO CALM?

17:54.120 --> 17:56.957
BECAUSE I INTEND
TO LIVE LONG ENOUGH

17:56.957 --> 17:59.860
TO SEE THAT
THAT SON OF A BITCH PAYS.

17:59.860 --> 18:03.303
AND DON'T LOOK AT ME
LIKE THAT.

18:03.303 --> 18:05.405
I MET HIS MOTHER.

18:05.405 --> 18:09.075
SHE IS A BITCH.

18:13.580 --> 18:15.281
TEA?

18:20.921 --> 18:22.122
[ SIGHS ]

18:22.122 --> 18:23.223
[ GASPS ]

18:23.223 --> 18:24.925
WHAT ARE YOU ‐‐ NO.
I WANT TO SPEAK ‐‐

18:24.925 --> 18:26.059
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

18:26.059 --> 18:27.327
I WANT TO SPEAK
TO WYATT.

18:27.327 --> 18:28.361
NO, NO. I'M SORRY.

18:28.361 --> 18:31.064
I WANT TO SPEAK TO HIM
NOW!

18:31.064 --> 18:32.699
HE CAN'T.
HE CANNOT HAVE THIS ‐‐

18:32.699 --> 18:34.267
I WANT TO SPEAK TO HIM
NOW.

18:35.368 --> 18:36.402
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
HERE?

18:36.402 --> 18:37.804
I DID NOT DESERVE
THAT MESSAGE

18:37.804 --> 18:39.072
THAT YOU LEFT
ON MY PHONE.

18:39.072 --> 18:40.073
THAT WAS SO CRUEL.

18:40.073 --> 18:41.775
GET OUT OF HERE.
YEAH. YOU HEARD HIM.

18:41.775 --> 18:42.776
GET OUT.

18:42.776 --> 18:44.177
WHY ARE YOU TREATING ME
THIS WAY?

18:44.177 --> 18:45.478
WHY AM I TREATING YOU
THIS WAY?

18:45.478 --> 18:46.847
WHY ARE YOU TREATING ME
THIS WAY?

18:46.847 --> 18:48.048
I DID NOTHING TO YOU,
LAURA.

18:48.048 --> 18:49.816
WELL, I DID NOTHING TO YOU.

18:49.816 --> 18:50.917
WHAT?

18:50.917 --> 18:52.052
YOU STOOD ME UP.

18:52.052 --> 18:54.120
YOU WON'T RETURN MY CALLS.

18:54.120 --> 18:55.188
AM I RIGHT?

18:57.958 --> 18:59.492
AM I RIGHT?

19:01.001 --> 19:02.703
YES.

19:02.703 --> 19:04.971
AND YOU TOLD ME
YOU WEREN'T SEEING ANYONE.

19:06.072 --> 19:07.107
I'M NOT.

19:07.107 --> 19:08.374
YES, YOU ARE.

19:08.374 --> 19:09.776
NO, I'M NOT.

19:09.776 --> 19:11.244
YOU'RE SEEING BRADLEY.

19:11.244 --> 19:12.546
NO, I'M NOT.

19:12.546 --> 19:15.015
YOU'RE LYING TO ME.
JEFFREY SAW YOU.

19:17.551 --> 19:18.552
TELL HER, JEFFREY.
I'M SORRY.

19:18.552 --> 19:19.720
WHAT IS HE SAYING TO ME?

19:19.720 --> 19:20.754
TELL HER, JEFFREY.

19:25.058 --> 19:28.228
YES, I‐I SAW YOU WITH HIM,
AND I‐I TOLD WYATT.

19:28.228 --> 19:31.064
WHAT ARE YOU ‐‐
WHAT ARE YOU EVEN TALKING ABOUT?

19:31.064 --> 19:33.567
BRADLEY HAS BEEN IN MAINE
WITH HIS FATHER.

19:33.567 --> 19:35.969
HE'S BEEN THERE FOR YEARS.

19:35.969 --> 19:37.738
WHAT?
YEAH.

19:37.738 --> 19:39.573
HE LEFT OUR JUNIOR YEAR
IN HIGH SCHOOL.

19:39.573 --> 19:41.007
I HAVEN'T SPOKEN
TO HIM SINCE.

19:43.677 --> 19:45.111
OKAY, UM...
YOU KNOW WHAT?

19:45.111 --> 19:47.714
JUST ‐‐ JUST LEAVE, LAURA.
IT'S TIME FOR YOU TO LEAVE.

19:47.714 --> 19:49.750
HE'S ‐‐
HE'S LYING TO YOU.

19:50.884 --> 19:52.586
HE LIED TO YOU.
NO. NO.

19:52.586 --> 19:53.587
YEAH, YOU DID.

19:53.587 --> 19:54.688
NO.

19:54.688 --> 19:56.189
HE TOLD ME NOT TO CALL YOU,

19:56.189 --> 19:57.357
AND THAT HE WAS
GONNA TELL YOU

19:57.357 --> 19:58.759
THAT I COULDN'T MAKE IT
FOR DINNER.

19:58.759 --> 20:00.126
W‐W‐WHY ARE YOU
SAYING THAT?

20:00.126 --> 20:02.102
ARE YOU TRYING TO MAKE ME
LOOK LIKE THE LIAR?

20:02.102 --> 20:03.804
WYATT, LISTEN TO ME.
HE IS LYING TO YOU.

20:03.804 --> 20:05.806
[ Voice breaking ]
HE TOLD ME THAT I'M BAD FOR YOU

20:05.806 --> 20:08.642
AND THAT I SHOULDN'T SEE YOU
FOR A WHOLE YEAR.

20:08.642 --> 20:10.276
HE'S TOLD ME TO IGNORE YOU.

20:10.276 --> 20:11.812
ARE YOU REALLY GONNA
LIE LIKE THIS?

20:13.046 --> 20:15.148
WYATT, YOU KNOW ME.
YOU KNOW I WOULDN'T DO ‐‐

20:15.148 --> 20:16.216
YOU KNOW HOW MUCH I...

20:16.216 --> 20:17.618
YOU ‐‐
I WOULDN'T DO THAT.

20:17.618 --> 20:19.252
LISTEN TO ME.

20:19.252 --> 20:21.421
YOU KNOW ME. YOU KNOW ME.

20:21.421 --> 20:24.224
HE'S LYING TO YOU.

20:41.875 --> 20:44.077
YOU NEED TO LEAVE,
ALL RIGHT?

20:44.077 --> 20:46.580
I TOLD YOU
HE CAN'T HAVE VISITORS.

20:46.580 --> 20:48.582
I ONLY HOPE
THIS DOESN'T SET HIM BACK.

20:48.582 --> 20:50.183
IF HE DOESN'T GET
ANY BETTER,

20:50.183 --> 20:51.818
JUST KNOW THAT THIS IS
ALL YOUR FAULT.

20:51.818 --> 20:53.419
IS MY FAULT?
MY FAULT?

20:53.419 --> 20:55.455
I DIDN'T COME IN HERE
LIKE AN ENRAGED LUNATIC.

20:55.455 --> 20:57.023
YOU DID.

20:58.959 --> 21:01.167
LISTEN, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOUR PROBLEM IS.

21:01.167 --> 21:02.503
YOU KNOW THAT I LOVE HIM,

21:02.503 --> 21:04.838
AND I DON'T KNOW WHY
YOU'RE TRYING TO SABOTAGE THIS,

21:04.838 --> 21:06.773
BUT YOU'RE A MEAN PERSON.

21:06.773 --> 21:08.942
YOU'RE A MEAN, CRUEL PERSON,

21:08.942 --> 21:12.946
AND I DON'T WANT YOU
TO EVER SPEAK TO ME EVER AGAIN.

21:12.946 --> 21:14.815
YOU GOT THAT?

21:14.815 --> 21:16.249
GET IT THROUGH YOUR HEAD.

21:35.536 --> 21:37.604
WHAT'S TAKING HER
SO LONG?

21:37.604 --> 21:39.773
SHE SAID SHE WAS GONNA
MEET WITH THE JUDGE

21:39.773 --> 21:41.675
AND THEN SHE WAS
GONNA MEET US HERE.

21:41.675 --> 21:44.110
COME ON, NOW.
RELAX, BABY.

21:45.311 --> 21:47.180
WHAT IF HE DOESN'T
GIVE HER THE BAIL?

21:47.180 --> 21:48.649
NO, HE WILL.

21:48.649 --> 21:50.651
CALM DOWN.

21:50.651 --> 21:52.653
[ SIGHS ]

21:52.653 --> 21:53.787
ALL RIGHT, LOOK.

21:53.787 --> 21:55.221
IF I GOT TO STAY IN HERE,
THEN ‐‐

21:55.221 --> 21:56.723
DON'T TALK LIKE THAT,
BENNY.

21:56.723 --> 21:57.691
MAMA, LISTEN TO ME ‐‐

21:57.691 --> 21:58.992
NO, I'M NOT
LISTENING TO YOU.

21:58.992 --> 22:00.594
LISTEN TO ME.
HEAR ME, ALL RIGHT?

22:00.594 --> 22:02.703
IF I GOT TO STAY IN
HERE, YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE TO SELL MY TRUCK.

22:02.703 --> 22:04.004
BENNY.

22:04.004 --> 22:05.405
THE TITLE
IS IN MY BOTTOM DRAWER

22:05.405 --> 22:06.940
ON THE RIGHT‐HAND SIDE
IN MY ROOM.

22:06.940 --> 22:08.474
BENNY, I WILL NOT BE
SELLING YOUR TRUCK

22:08.474 --> 22:09.943
BECAUSE YOU'RE GONNA
GET OUT OF HERE.

22:11.144 --> 22:12.813
[ SIGHS ]
I HOPE YOU'RE RIGHT.

22:12.813 --> 22:14.147
I AM RIGHT.

22:14.147 --> 22:16.850
WHAT HAPPENED?

22:18.484 --> 22:20.721
YOU ARE GOING HOME.

22:20.721 --> 22:22.022
OH, GOD.
REALLY?

22:22.022 --> 22:23.023
I AM?

22:23.023 --> 22:24.090
YES.
WHEN?

22:24.090 --> 22:25.125
RIGHT NOW.

22:25.125 --> 22:26.226
OH, MY GOD.

22:26.226 --> 22:28.128
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

22:28.128 --> 22:30.631
THANK YOU.
THANK YOU, MS. VERONICA.

22:30.631 --> 22:32.398
NO NEED TO THANK ME.

22:32.398 --> 22:34.134
YES, THERE IS.
SO, I'M GOING HOME?

22:34.134 --> 22:35.335
YES!

22:35.335 --> 22:36.903
UNLESS
YOU WANT TO STAY HERE.

22:36.903 --> 22:38.104
HELL, NO.

22:38.104 --> 22:39.840
NO. [ LAUGHS ]

22:39.840 --> 22:41.742
NOW, IS THIS BAIL?

22:41.742 --> 22:42.809
NO.

22:42.809 --> 22:44.377
ALL CHARGES
HAVE BEEN DROPPED.

22:44.377 --> 22:45.712
WHAT?

22:45.712 --> 22:47.981
APPARENTLY, ALL THE EVIDENCE
WENT MISSING,

22:47.981 --> 22:49.983
SO THE D. A. HAD TO
DROP THE CHARGES.

22:49.983 --> 22:51.885
OH, MY GOD.
THANK YOU, JESUS.

22:51.885 --> 22:54.454
[ LAUGHS ] OH!

22:54.454 --> 22:55.989
SO, COME ON.

22:55.989 --> 22:57.023
LET'S GET YOU HOME.

22:57.023 --> 22:59.025
OFFICER,
OPEN THIS DOOR PLEASE.

23:00.393 --> 23:02.503
THANK YOU.

23:04.237 --> 23:05.839
[ SQUEALS ]
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:07.373 --> 23:09.510
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

23:21.454 --> 23:23.890
AMANDA, IS THAT YOU?

23:28.862 --> 23:30.864
YEAH.

23:30.864 --> 23:32.365
TALK TO ME.

23:32.365 --> 23:33.767
[ SIGHS ]

23:33.767 --> 23:34.968
HI.

23:34.968 --> 23:36.336
HI.

23:36.336 --> 23:38.138
ARE YOU FEELING OKAY?

23:38.138 --> 23:39.806
YES. WHY DO YOU ASK?

23:39.806 --> 23:42.543
I HAVEN'T SEEN YOU
STAYING IN BED THIS LONG

23:42.543 --> 23:43.910
UNLESS YOU WERE SICK.

23:45.245 --> 23:47.548
I'M FINE.
I JUST NEED SOME REST.

23:49.382 --> 23:52.118
I SHOULD BE ASKING YOU,
HOW ARE YOU DOING?

23:52.118 --> 23:54.454
I'M FINE.

23:54.454 --> 23:56.356
NO, YOU'RE NOT.

23:56.356 --> 23:58.992
DAD ALREADY TALKED TO ME
ABOUT THIS.

24:00.093 --> 24:01.167
DID HE, NOW?

24:01.167 --> 24:02.769
MM‐HMM.

24:03.870 --> 24:06.439
AND WHAT DID DADDY SAY?

24:06.439 --> 24:08.208
BECAUSE I'M CLUELESS.

24:08.208 --> 24:11.011
HE WANTS ME
TO SEE A THERAPIST.

24:11.011 --> 24:12.813
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

24:12.813 --> 24:15.181
I DON'T NEED A THERAPIST.

24:15.181 --> 24:18.619
YOU NEED SOMETHING IF YOU'RE
GONNA LEARN HOW TO COPE.

24:18.619 --> 24:19.986
SOMETHING LIKE WHAT?

24:19.986 --> 24:21.655
DRUGS?

24:21.655 --> 24:24.224
THAT WOULD BE YOUR BROTHER.

24:24.224 --> 24:27.661
OR MAYBE A WHOLE LOT OF BOURBON
THROUGHOUT THE DAY.

24:29.630 --> 24:31.865
IS THAT A REFERENCE TO ME?

24:31.865 --> 24:33.934
MAYBE.

24:33.934 --> 24:35.902
MY, MY, MY.

24:38.438 --> 24:41.542
LOOK WHO CAME OUT OF
THE HOSPITAL WITH A BACKBONE.

24:41.542 --> 24:44.210
I WAS JUST STATING
THE OBVIOUS.

24:44.210 --> 24:45.879
WHAT'S OBVIOUS TO ME,
AMANDA,

24:45.879 --> 24:48.214
IS THAT YOU'RE IN NEED
OF SOME SERIOUS HELP.

24:48.214 --> 24:50.383
I HAVE HELP.

24:50.383 --> 24:51.752
DO YOU?

24:51.752 --> 24:52.853
YEAH.

24:56.957 --> 24:58.659
FROM WHOM?

25:01.034 --> 25:02.736
CANDACE.

25:02.736 --> 25:04.905
SHE HELPS ME.

25:06.507 --> 25:08.308
DOES SHE, NOW?

25:08.308 --> 25:09.610
YEAH.

25:09.610 --> 25:11.044
SHE HELPS ME A LOT.

25:11.044 --> 25:12.412
I'M SURE SHE DOES.

25:12.412 --> 25:14.214
SHE'S A GOOD FRIEND.

25:14.214 --> 25:15.716
[ SIGHS ]

25:15.716 --> 25:17.117
YEAH.

25:17.117 --> 25:19.152
WE HAVE AN APARTMENT
TOGETHER OFF CAMPUS.

25:19.152 --> 25:20.721
WE'RE ROOMMATES.

25:20.721 --> 25:23.256
THAT SO?

25:24.324 --> 25:26.560
YEAH.
AND I'M GETTING OUT OF HERE.

25:26.560 --> 25:28.595
OH, WHEN?

25:30.130 --> 25:31.497
NOW.

25:31.497 --> 25:32.833
I'M GOING HOME.

25:32.833 --> 25:34.635
NO, YOU'RE NOT.

25:34.635 --> 25:36.136
YES, I AM.

25:36.136 --> 25:37.403
NO, YOU'RE NOT.

25:37.403 --> 25:39.005
I'M OVER 21.

25:39.005 --> 25:41.174
YOU CAN'T TELL ME
WHAT TO DO ANYMORE.

25:44.144 --> 25:45.746
YOU'RE RIGHT.

25:46.847 --> 25:48.582
YOU'RE RIGHT.

25:49.816 --> 25:53.319
YOU CAN DO WHATEVER
YOU WANT TO DO.

25:53.319 --> 25:56.056
GOOD, BECAUSE
I'M LEAVING LAW SCHOOL

25:56.056 --> 25:58.759
AND I'M GOING TO DESIGN SCHOOL,
JUST AS I SAID.

25:58.759 --> 26:00.867
OKAY.

26:03.269 --> 26:04.705
OKAY?

26:04.705 --> 26:07.107
THAT'S ALL
YOU'RE GONNA SAY?

26:09.009 --> 26:11.712
YES.
I'M FINE WITH IT.

26:11.712 --> 26:14.214
JUST GO ON
AND LIVE YOUR LIFE.

26:14.214 --> 26:15.716
FINE.

26:15.716 --> 26:20.854
AND, AMANDA, WHILE YOU'RE
LIVING YOUR LIFE WITH NINE...

26:20.854 --> 26:23.089
WHAT? WHAT'S NINE?

26:24.224 --> 26:28.461
IT'S THE NAME I HAVE
FOR YOUR FRIEND ‐‐ NINE.

26:28.461 --> 26:30.330
WHY DO YOU CALL HER THAT?

26:30.330 --> 26:32.799
WHY DON'T YOU ASK HER?

26:32.799 --> 26:33.967
I WILL.

26:33.967 --> 26:36.737
AND WHILE YOU'RE AT IT,

26:36.737 --> 26:39.973
WHY DON'T YOU ASK HER
WHERE SHE CAN GET YOU A JOB...

26:39.973 --> 26:42.976
BECAUSE THE MINUTE
YOU WALK OUT THAT DOOR,

26:42.976 --> 26:44.878
YOU ARE OFFICIALLY CUT OFF.

26:44.878 --> 26:47.981
NOT A DIME OF MY MONEY
WILL FOLLOW YOU.

26:49.215 --> 26:51.017
YOU CAN'T CONTROL ME
WITH MONEY, MOM.

26:51.017 --> 26:54.254
I AM NOT TRYING
TO CONTROL YOU, AMANDA.

26:54.254 --> 26:56.289
I'M TRYING TO HELP YOU.

26:57.924 --> 27:00.326
HELP ME.
HELP ME HOW?

27:00.326 --> 27:03.670
LITTLE GIRL, YOU HAVE NO IDEA
THE DANGER YOU ARE IN.

27:03.670 --> 27:05.806
[ SNIFFS ]

27:05.806 --> 27:07.774
THAT GIRL IS BAD NEWS.

27:07.774 --> 27:10.176
YOU JUST DON'T LIKE HER.

27:10.176 --> 27:13.479
OH...
YOU'RE RIGHT ABOUT THAT.

27:14.815 --> 27:16.282
YOU DON'T KNOW HER.

27:16.282 --> 27:17.751
OH, I KNOW HER
WELL ENOUGH

27:17.751 --> 27:19.620
TO KNOW
THAT SHE IS NOT YOUR FRIEND.

27:19.620 --> 27:22.589
YOU ARE A PAWN,
AND YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW IT.

27:22.589 --> 27:24.525
SO YOU THINK
I'M STUPID, TOO?

27:24.525 --> 27:25.526
NO.

27:25.526 --> 27:27.528
I THINK YOU'RE NAIVE.

27:27.528 --> 27:29.596
THERE'S A DIFFERENCE.

27:29.596 --> 27:31.932
LET ME TELL YOU
HOW SMART I AM.

27:31.932 --> 27:33.967
I KNOW THAT GRANDDAD
LEFT ME A TRUST,

27:33.967 --> 27:35.769
AND I SHOULD HAVE HAD IT
BY NOW.

27:35.769 --> 27:37.538
SO, IF YOU DON'T GIVE IT
TO ME,

27:37.538 --> 27:39.906
I GUESS I'LL JUST HAVE TO
GET IT ANOTHER WAY.

27:39.906 --> 27:43.443
SO, YOU REALLY HAVE BEEN
HANGING OUT WITH THAT GIRL?

27:43.443 --> 27:45.378
MM, MM, MM.

27:46.647 --> 27:49.149
I CAN SEE IT ALL OVER YOU.

27:55.288 --> 27:57.624
I'M NOT AFRAID OF YOU
ANYMORE.

27:57.624 --> 28:01.167
DARLING, YOU DON'T NEED
TO BE AFRAID OF ME.

28:03.737 --> 28:06.339
YOU NEED TO BE WORRIED.

28:06.339 --> 28:08.441
GOODBYE, MOTHER.

28:20.120 --> 28:22.122
Hanna: YOU'RE HOME.

28:22.122 --> 28:24.490
[ LAUGHING ]

28:24.490 --> 28:26.727
MY TV!

28:26.727 --> 28:28.929
OH, MOM, IT FEELS
SO GOOD TO BE HOME.

28:28.929 --> 28:31.732
I BET IT DOES, BABY.
WHOO!

28:31.732 --> 28:34.100
THANK YOU, GOD!

28:34.100 --> 28:36.302
AND THEY DROPPED
THE CHARGES.

28:36.302 --> 28:38.238
OH, BENNY,
WHAT'D I TELL YOU?

28:38.238 --> 28:39.272
AIN'T GOD GOOD?

28:39.272 --> 28:40.340
GOD IS GREAT.

28:40.340 --> 28:41.942
YES, HE IS.

28:41.942 --> 28:44.344
OH, I'M GOING TO MAKE
ALL YOUR FAVORITES TONIGHT.

28:44.344 --> 28:45.912
THANK YOU.
I'M STARVING.

28:45.912 --> 28:48.915
OH, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO DO FIRST.

28:48.915 --> 28:50.617
SHOOT, I DO.

28:50.617 --> 28:52.018
AND WHAT'S THAT?

28:52.018 --> 28:53.854
TAKE A LONG SHOWER.
FOR HOW LONG?

28:53.854 --> 28:55.255
LONG ENOUGH
TO GET CLEAN.

28:55.255 --> 28:56.456
OH, NO, SIR.

28:56.456 --> 28:59.059
I DON'T KNOW IF I'M GONNA
LET YOU OUT OF MY SIGHT.

28:59.059 --> 29:00.861
[ LAUGHING ] OH!

29:00.861 --> 29:02.969
MA, SERIOUSLY, COME ON,
I GOT TO TAKE A BATH.

29:02.969 --> 29:04.137
OH! YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

29:04.137 --> 29:06.039
YOU SURE DO. GO ON!
WHAT HAPPENED?

29:06.039 --> 29:07.908
I THOUGHT YOU SAID
YOU MISSED ME.

29:07.908 --> 29:10.243
I DID MISS YOU,
BUT I AIN'T MISS THEM PITS.

29:10.243 --> 29:12.478
[ Laughing ]
GET AWAY FROM ME.

29:12.478 --> 29:14.447
[ LAUGHS ]

29:14.447 --> 29:17.417
WHEW!
RUN TO THE WATER.

29:29.530 --> 29:31.832
BENNY: Hello?

29:31.832 --> 29:33.834
BENNY?

29:33.834 --> 29:35.035
I'M OUT.

29:35.035 --> 29:37.070
[ CHUCKLES ] OH, MY GOD.

29:37.070 --> 29:38.739
THAT IS SO GREAT.

29:38.739 --> 29:39.873
Yeah.

29:39.873 --> 29:42.008
UM...

29:42.008 --> 29:43.476
WHEN CAN I SEE YOU?

29:43.476 --> 29:44.578
YOU CAN COME SEE ME
TOMORROW.

29:44.578 --> 29:46.046
MAMA'S GOING TO MAKE ME
SOME DINNER TONIGHT.

29:46.046 --> 29:48.081
BENNY,
I'M SO GLAD YOU'RE OUT.

29:48.081 --> 29:49.315
